{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d7a532c-2f89-4fe2-a22d-80e0b5aef429","content":"The issue is classic F# — **file compilation order matters**. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. Let me fix the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_L3VJdjhK9zgc3gkVU8BvLI","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f5f755986d314754bb6a980af7498d00/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f5f755986d314754bb6a980af7498d00/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4f2240d0-4b80-402f-b63c-57607e8c526c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should come last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. \n`Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":448,"requestId":"281A:18B6D6:1C91821:1F9952E:69FA8F78"},"id":"18a5e2b7-ef51-4621-8ac8-e6a67423602d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:57.847Z","parentId":"3d12cc06-fb63-4a75-877b-469a371bf75a"}
